66615.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iue1665702766615.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/iue1665702766615.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"iue1665702766615\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      clrmess\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"iue1665702766615__clrmess_66026\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Declare how the message frame is cleared. </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"iue1665702766615__topic_d19214e1_d19215e1_d19216e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iue1665702766615__p_d19217e1_d19218e1_d19219e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CLRmess</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iue1665702766615__topic_d13822e1_d13823e1_d13824e1_d13825e1_d13826e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d801018e68\">\n                        \n Arguments\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"iue1665702766615__li_d9437e1_d9438e1_d9439e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code>—message frame is cleared\n               normally. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"iue1665702766615__li_d9440e1_d9441e1_d9442e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>—message frame is not cleared, and messages are allowed to accumulate in the message frame.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iue1665702766615__topic_d13827e1_d13828e1_d13829e1_d13830e1_d13831e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d801018e88\">\n                        \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"iue1665702766615__p_d19226e1_d19227e1_d19228e1\">It is sometimes useful to have messages accumulate in the message frame to get a complete picture of how a component is operating.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"iue1665702766615__section_gmh_fgb_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d801018e97\">Example:</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"iue1665702766615__pre_q3s_ggb_tcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">clr off</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528711\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528711\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "clrmess Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 16, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 clrmess Declare how the message frame is cleared. CLRmess on | off Arguments on —message frame is cleared normally. off —message frame is not cleared, and messages are allowed to accumulate in the message frame. Description It is sometimes useful to have messages accumulate in the message frame to get a complete picture of how a component is operating. Example: clr off Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}